Answer: \section{Mark Twain}

Mark Twain (1835-1910) was an American author and humorist. He is best known for his novels, The Adventures of Tom Sawyer (1876) and its sequel, Adventures of Huckleberry Finn (1885), the latter often called the Great American Novel.

